name: Apple
summary: Apple unveiled "Apple Intelligence," a new suite of AI-powered features coming to iPhones, iPads, and Macs. Experts at CNET noted that while these features automate tasks, some users may find them unnecessary or intrusive. TechRadar praised Apple's Vision Pro headset for its revolutionary technology, but lamented its limited usage. Bloomberg anticipates significant updates in AI, iPadOS, and macOS at Apple's upcoming WWDC 2024 conference. Apple itself highlighted the personalization and intelligence enhancements in iOS 18. After experiencing WWDC, CNET reconsidered its initial skepticism about iOS 18. Apple Intelligence and iOS 18 previews provide further insights into upcoming features. The company also announced updates to its services and the winners of its 2024 Design Awards.

name: Crux
summary: Specialized has unveiled its new Crux DSW gravel bike, touted as the lightest alloy gravel frame in the world, weighing under 1.4kg. The bike's sub-10kg weight and advanced features, including D'Aluisio Smartweld technology, make it a versatile option for gravel, cyclocross, and road riding. Critics have praised the Crux DSW for its impressive weight-to-performance ratio, describing it as the ideal "n-1" bike for cyclists seeking a single bike to handle multiple disciplines.
